_2529764\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 07, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104lwh1665702990671.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/lwh1665702990671.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/lwh1665702990671.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"lwh1665702990671\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Creating a Custom Print Dialog\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">You can create your own print dialog box that includes an operation to handle printing.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"lwh1665702990671__context_w2431ab1b5b1_w2432ab1b5_w2433ab1\">\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"lwh1665702990671__topic_d65123e1_d65124e1_d65125e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lwh1665702990671__p_d65126e1_d65127e1_d65128e1\">This operation will incorporate the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">print</span> statement, which requires the following information:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">print {<var class=\"keyword varname\">PrintJobModel</var> {,<var class=\"keyword varname\">PrintMode</var> {,<var class=\"keyword varname\">Settings</var>}}}</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lwh1665702990671__p_d65129e1_d65130e1_d65131e1\">To create a custom print dialog box:</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"lwh1665702990671__li_d28250e1_d28251e1_d28252e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Create a Print dialog box as a modal form.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"lwh1665702990671__li_d28253e1_d28254e1_d28255e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"lwh1665702990671__p_d65132e1_d65133e1_d65134e1\">Define an operation similar to the following: </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">operation MYPRINT\nparams\n string $PRINTSETTINGS$ : INOUT\nendparams\n...</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">$PRINTSETTINGS$</code>is a component variable containing an associative\n                  list. Default print settings can be passed to the Print dialog by\n                     <code class=\"ph codeph\">$PRINTSETTINGS$</code>, and the modified print settings can be\n                  returned to the form by the same parameter.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lwh1665702990671__p_d65135e1_d65136e1_d65137e1\">The dialog box only has to return information\n                  about <var class=\"keyword varname\">PrintJobModel</var>, <var class=\"keyword varname\">PrintMode</var>and\n                     <var class=\"keyword varname\">Settings</var>This is because <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/ask</span>is redundant\n                  in a custom print dialog box, and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">print</span>\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/preview</span>should be activated directly from the parent form and\n                  not from the Print dialog, as the data required to build the print preview is not\n                  available in the Print dialog.</p>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"lwh1665702990671__li_d28256e1_d28257e1_d28258e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"lwh1665702990671__p_d65138e1_d65139e1_d65140e1\">Enable the form to specify print settings, using\n               print job models or third-party software. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">When making exclusive use of print job models, do the following:</div>\n<ol class=\"ol substeps\" type=\"a\">\n<li class=\"li substep\" id=\"lwh1665702990671__li_d28259e1_d28260e1_d28261e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Create a drop-down list of available print job models, using a ValRep in the\n                     format of <var class=\"keyword varname\">PrintJobModel</var>=<var class=\"keyword varname\">DescriptiveText</var>.\n                  </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep\" id=\"lwh1665702990671__li_d28262e1_d28263e1_d28264e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Create a drop-down list to select <var class=\"keyword varname\">PrintMode</var>. </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep\" id=\"lwh1665702990671__li_d28265e1_d28266e1_d28267e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Create a field to set the value for <var class=\"keyword varname\">Settings</var>. </span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li substep\" id=\"lwh1665702990671__li_d28268e1_d28269e1_d28270e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Return the user’s choices to the parent form by\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">$PRINTSETTINGS$</code>. Process the list to provide\n                        <var class=\"keyword varname\">PrintJobModel</var>, <var class=\"keyword varname\">PrintMode</var>, and\n                        <var class=\"keyword varname\">Settings</var> information to the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">print</span>\n                     statement. </span>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</li></ol></section>\n<section class=\"section result body required-cleanup-multiple-ol-elements-in-topic-body\" id=\"lwh1665702990671__result_w2434ab1b5b5_w2435ab1b5_w2436ab1\">\n<div class=\"sectiondiv postreq\" id=\"lwh1665702990671__topic_d65141e1_d65142e1_d65143e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lwh1665702990671__p_d65144e1_d65145e1_d65146e1\">To extend the custom print dialog box to use a third-party DLL to change Microsoft Windows printer settings. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vyz1665702990742.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vyz1665702990742.html\" title=\"You can extend the custom print dialog box to use a third-party DLL to change Microsoft Windows printer settings.\">Use Third-Party DLLs in a Custom Print Dialog</a>.</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hbo1720163290270.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>print</a><p>Activate printing.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529764\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529764\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Creating a Custom Print Dialog Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 07, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Creating a Custom Print Dialog You can create your own print dialog box that includes an operation to handle printing. This operation will incorporate the print statement, which requires the following information: print { PrintJobModel {, PrintMode {, Settings }}} Copy To create a custom print dialog box: Create a Print dialog box as a modal form. Define an operation similar to the following: operation MYPRINT params string $PRINTSETTINGS$ : INOUT endparams ... Copy $PRINTSETTINGS$ is a component variable containing an associative list. Default print settings can be passed to the Print dialog by $PRINTSETTINGS$ , and the modified print settings can be returned to the form by the same parameter. The dialog box only has to return information about PrintJobModel , PrintMode and Settings This is because /ask is redundant in a custom print dialog box, and print /preview should be activated directly from the parent form and not from the Print dialog, as the data required to build the print preview is not available in the Print dialog. Enable the form to specify print settings, using print job models or third-party software. When making exclusive use of print job models, do the following: Create a drop-down list of available print job models, using a ValRep in the format of PrintJobModel = DescriptiveText . Create a drop-down list to select PrintMode . Create a field to set the value for Settings . Return the user’s choices to the parent form by $PRINTSETTINGS$ . Process the list to provide PrintJobModel , PrintMode , and Settings information to the print statement. To extend the custom print dialog box to use a third-party DLL to change Microsoft Windows printer settings. For more information, see Use Third-Party DLLs in a Custom Print Dialog . Related Links print Activate printing. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}